Subject: Re: [T2] Freaky Electrical Problem on '68 Bus

Just a guess, but I would check the dimmer relay. The headlight switch sends
power runs through the dimmer relay en route to the high and low beams.
Turning the lights off and on may jolt a failing dimmer relay unshorting it
for a while.

Cheers,

John Rogers '70 Westy (Proud Mary)


